                        <additions><lb/>
                            <label>Inscription:</label> The <locus from="ia" to="ia">first right
                                flyleaf a side (f. ia)</locus> bears a note describing the work,
                            probably in the hand of former owner <persName role=" ins fmo"
                                ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/" key="person_97751058">Alexander
                                Lindsay</persName>. <lb/>
                            <label>Bookplates:</label>
                            <locus from="Inner_back_cover" to="Inner_back_cover">Left
                                pastedown</locus>: <q xml:lang="en">Bibliotheca Lindesiana</q> with
                            shelfmark <q xml:lang="en">2/I</q>, and class mark <q xml:lang="en"
                                >Persian MSS <hi rend="strikethrough">84</hi></q> with the number
                            crossed out and <q xml:lang="en">878</q> written aside. </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding notBefore="1825" notAfter="1860">
                                <p>Probably rebound in <placeName
                                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7008653" cert="high"
                                        >Britain</placeName> in the <date>mid
                                    19th-centiry</date>.</p>
                                <p>Resewn on three recessed cords, with comparatively thin,
                                    buff-coloured stock added as endpapers. Edges trimmed and
                                    chevron endbands twined in yellow and silk threads over round
                                    cores as <locus from="Head" to="Head">head</locus> and <locus
                                        from="Tail" to="Tail">tail</locus>. Covereed in half
                                    crimson-coloured, straight-grained morocco goatskin
                                        <material>leather</material> over pasteboards, with
                                    'Spanish' wave-patterened marbled paper sides.</p>
                                <decoNote type="binding">Boards decoated with serrated lines in gold
                                    along the paper, and spine panels palleted with double fillet
                                    lines. </decoNote>
                                <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                                        <height>226</height>
                                        <width>137</width>
                                        <depth>15</depth>
                                    </dimensions></p>
                                <condition>Binding in good condition with minor abrasion to the
                                    exterior.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin change="#fix-dates">Probably completed in the <origPlace cert="high"
                                ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208" key="place_7000208"
                                >Indian subcontinent</origPlace> undated, but <date cert="high"
                                from="1850" to="1868">probably mid-19th century</date> given the use
                            of wove paper</origin>
                        <provenance><p>While the circumstances under which this volume arrived in
                                Britain remain unclear, <persName role=" ins fmo"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/" key="person_97751058"
                                    >Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford (1812–1880)</persName>
                                eventually acquire it from an unidentified source for his <orgName
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/295427552" key="person_295427552"
                                    >Bibliotheca Lindesiana</orgName> at Haigh Hall, <placeName
                                    ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7010384"
                                    key="place_7010384">Wigan</placeName>.</p></provenance>

                        <provenance><p>Purchased by <persName role="dnr" key="person_f6379"
                                    change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName>
                                in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date> from
                                    <persName role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/"
                                    key="person_9985420">James Ludovic Lindsay, 26th Earl of
                                    Crawford (1847–1913)</persName>.</p></provenance>
                        <acquisition>
